{{DISPLAYTITLE:''The Equinox of the Gods'' (Crowley)}}
[[Image:Aleister Crowley - The Equinox of the Gods cover.jpg|right|thumb|Cover art of 1991 edition]]
'''''The Equinox of the Gods''''' ({{ISBN|1-56184-028-9}}) is a book first published in 1936 detailing the events and circumstances leading up to [[Aleister Crowley]]'s transcription of ''[[The Book of the Law]]'', the central text of [[Thelema]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://hermetic.com/crowley/equinox-of-the-gods/eqotgs.html |title = The Equinox of the Gods, The Summons | date = September 1936 | author = Aleister Crowley |accessdate =  October 19, 2011}}</ref>

Included in ''The Equinox of the Gods'' are a facsimile of Crowley's handwritten manuscript of ''The Book of the Law'', personal diary extracts, and a full color reproduction of the [[Stèle of Revealing]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://hermetic.com/crowley/equinox-of-the-gods/eqotg7.html | date = September 1936 |author = Aleister Crowley |title = The Equinox of the Gods, Chapter 7 |accessdate = October 19, 2011}}</ref>

