{{italic title}}
'''''The Tale of Orpheus and Erudices his Quene''''' is a poem by the [[Scotland|Scottish]] [[northern renaissance]] poet [[Robert Henryson]] that adapts and develops the Greek myth which most famously appears in two classic Latin texts, the ''[[Metamorphoses]]'' of [[Ovid]] and the ''[[Georgics]]'' of [[Virgil]]. 

[[Image:Orpheus, Eurydice and Aristaeus by Jacopo del Sellaio.jpg|370px|thumb|left|[[Jacopo del Sellaio]], ''Orpheus and Eurydice'', c.1480]]
